<title>FRANCE: France, Germany agree on need for EU work on taxes.</title>
<headline>France, Germany agree on need for EU work on taxes.</headline>
<dateline>LYON, France 1997-03-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>French Finance Minister Jean Arthuis said on Wednesday he and German Finance Minister Theo Waigel agreed on the need for the European Union to make further efforts to get rid of tax anomalies which create unfair competition.</p>
<p>He said there should be a code of good conduct to prevent countries gaining an unfair competitive advantage from their tax legislation and promised to press the European Commission to take action on the issue.</p>
<p>&quot;We cannot tolerate these forms of unfair competition. It is the future of the European Union which is at stake,&quot; he told a news conference after a meeting of the French and German finance ministers and central bank heads.</p>
</text>
